# SRP - Single Responsibility Principle

## Definition

A class should have only one reason to change.

OR

A class should have only one responsibility.

---

## Why SRP?

When a class performs multiple tasks:

- Difficult to maintain
- Difficult to test
- Difficult to debug
- Difficult to reuse

SRP helps us separate responsibilities into different classes.

---

## Bad Example

Employee class handling:

- Employee Details
- Salary Calculation
- Database Storage
- Email Notification